==English==
===Etymology===
[[barley]] + [[corn]]

===Noun===
# a [[grain]] of [[barley]]
# (''British, obsolete'') a unit of length equal to 1/3 [[inch]] (8mm), or sometimes 1/4 inch (6mm).
# (''architecture. woodworking'') a small groove between two [[moulding]]s
# In English tradition [[w:John Barleycorn|John Barleycorn]] personifies [[barley]] the source of [[malt]] and hence [[beer]] and [[whisky]].

